<br/>
<b>Satisfactory Savegame Tool</b> allows for numerous options regarding satisfactory
savegames, e.g. searching and erasing damaged entities.<br/>
<br/>
This tool is a complete C#/C++ port of former <b>Satisfactory Savegame Repairer</b>.<br/>
This tool is open source and available for free at
<a href='https://github.com/SillyBits/satisfactory-savegame-tool-ng/' target='_blank'>
Github</a> with ready-made installers available on the
<a href='https://github.com/SillyBits/satisfactory-savegame-tool-ng/releases' target='_blank'>
release</a> page. There's also a small
<a href='https://github.com/SillyBits/satisfactory-savegame-tool-ng/wiki' target='_blank'>
wiki</a> available which discusses basic aspects of this tool. License is GPL-v3, so you're
free to modify (fork) as you like. Also feel free to do pull requests for new functionality,
like special actions on a save not possible using the actions API embedded.<br/>
